1.	Mean-time to production is
  a.	How fast a new version of the application can be deployed into the production environment 
  b.	The average time it takes from when new software features are required until they are running in production.
  c.	How often a new release can be deployed into the production environment.
  d.	How long it takes applications in the production stage to recover from failure

2.	Average lead-time is
  a.	How often software fails during production
  b.	How long it takes for a new requirement to be delivered and deployed
  c.	How fast a new version of the application can be deployed into the production environment
  d.	The average time it takes from when new software features are required until they are running in production.

